{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id47727f0d-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7527"},"text":"§ 7527.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Advance payment of credit for health insurance costs of eligible individuals","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id47727f0e-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" General rule","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than the date that is 1 year after the date of the enactment of the Trade Adjustment Assistance Reauthorization Act of 2015, the Secretary shall establish a program for making payments on behalf of certified individuals to providers of qualified health insurance (as defined in section 35(e)) for such individuals.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id47727f0f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Limitation on advance payments during any taxable year","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may make payments under subsection (a) only to the extent that the total amount of such payments made on behalf of any individual during the taxable year does not exceed 72.5 percent of the amount paid by the taxpayer for coverage of the taxpayer and qualifying family members under qualified health insurance for eligible coverage months beginning in the taxable year.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id47727f10-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Certified individual","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this section, the term “certified individual” means any individual for whom a qualified health insurance costs credit eligibility certificate is in effect.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id47727f11-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Qualified health insurance costs eligibility certificate","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id47727f12-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this section, the term “qualified health insurance costs eligibility certificate” means any written statement that an individual is an eligible individual (as defined in section 35(c)) if such statement provides such information as the Secretary may require for purposes of this section and—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id47727f13-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/d/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of an eligible TAA recipient (as defined in section 35(c)(2)) or an eligible alternative TAA recipient (as defined in section 35(c)(3)), is certified by the Secretary of Labor (or by any other person or entity designated by the Secretary), or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id47727f14-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/d/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of an eligible PBGC pension recipient (as defined in section 35(c)(4)), is certified by the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation (or by any other person or entity designated by the Secretary).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id47727f15-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Inclusion of certain information","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of any statement described in paragraph (1), such statement shall not be treated as a qualified health insurance costs credit eligibility certificate unless such statement includes—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id47727f16-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/d/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the name, address, and telephone number of the State office or offices responsible for providing the individual with assistance with enrollment in qualified health insurance (as defined in section 35(e)),","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id47727f17-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/d/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a list of the coverage options that are treated as qualified health insurance (as so defined) by the State in which the individual resides, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id47727f18-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/d/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of a TAA-eligible individual (as defined in section 4980B(f)(5)(C)(iv)(II)), a statement informing the individual that the individual has 63 days from the date that is 7 days after the date of the issuance of such certificate to enroll in such insurance without a lapse in creditable coverage (as defined in section 9801(c)).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id47727f19-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Payment for premiums due prior to commencement of advance payments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id47727f1a-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The program established under subsection (a) shall provide that the Secretary shall make 1 or more retroactive payments on behalf of a certified individual in an aggregate amount equal to 72.5 percent of the premiums for coverage of the taxpayer and qualifying family members under qualified health insurance for eligible coverage months (as defined in section 35(b)) occurring—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id47727f1b-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/e/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" after the date that is 1 year after the date of the enactment of the Trade Adjustment Assistance Reauthorization Act of 2015; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id47727f1c-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/e/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" prior to the first month for which an advance payment is made on behalf of such individual under subsection (a).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id47727f1d-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s7527/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reduction of payment for amounts received under national emergency grants","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The amount of any payment determined under paragraph (1) shall be reduced by the amount of any payment made to the taxpayer for the purchase of qualified health insurance under a national emergency grant pursuant to section 173(f) of the Workforce Investment Act of 1998 (as in effect on the day before the date of enactment of the Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act) for a taxable year including the eligible coverage months described in paragraph (1).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id47727f1e-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/210/dA/tII/s202/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–210, div. A, title II, § 202(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-08-06"},"text":"Aug. 6, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/960"},"text":"116 Stat. 960","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/5/dB/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–5, div. B, title I","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1899A(a)(2), 1899B(a), 1899H(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-02-17"},"text":"Feb. 17, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/424"},"text":"123 Stat. 424","children":[],"tail":", 430; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/344/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–344, title I","children":[],"tail":", §§ 111(b), 112(a), 118(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/3615"},"text":"124 Stat. 3615","children":[],"tail":", 3616; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/40/tII/s241/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–40, title II, § 241(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/418"},"text":"125 Stat. 418","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128/tV/s512/r"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–128, title V, § 512(r)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/1712"},"text":"128 Stat. 1712","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/27/tIV/s407/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–27, title IV, § 407(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-06-29"},"text":"June 29, 2015","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/129/382"},"text":"129 Stat. 382","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id47727f1f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id47727f20-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id47727f21-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The date of the enactment of the Trade Adjustment Assistance Reauthorization Act of 2015, referred to in subsecs. (a) and (e)(1)(A), is the date of enactment of title IV of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/27"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–27","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-06-29"},"text":"June 29, 2015","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 173(f) of the Workforce Investment Act of 1998, referred to in subsec. (e)(2), was classified to former ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s2918/f"},"text":"section 2918(f) of Title 29","children":[],"tail":", Labor, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128/tV"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–128, title V","children":[],"tail":", §§ 506, 511(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/1703"},"text":"128 Stat. 1703","children":[],"tail":", 1705, effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 2015","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The date of enactment of the Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act, referred to in subsec. (e)(2), is the date of enactment of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–128","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 2014","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id47727f22-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2015—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/27/s407/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–27, § 407(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “the date that is 1 year after the date of the enactment of the Trade Adjustment Assistance Reauthorization Act of 2015” for “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-08-01"},"text":"August 1, 2003","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/27/s407/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–27, § 407(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “occurring—” for “occurring prior to the first month for which an advance payment is made on behalf of such individual under subsection (a).” and added subpars. (A) and (B)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2014—Subsec. (e)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–128","children":[],"tail":" inserted “(as in effect on the day before the date of enactment of the Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act)” after “of 1998”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/40/s241/b/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–40, § 241(b)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “72.5 percent” for “65 percent (80 percent in the case of eligible coverage months beginning before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-02-13"},"text":"February 13, 2011","children":[],"tail":")”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/40/s241/b/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–40, § 241(b)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “which is issued before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-02-13"},"text":"February 13, 2011","children":[],"tail":"” after “in paragraph (1)” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/40/s241/b/2/D"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–40, § 241(b)(2)(D)","children":[],"tail":", struck out introductory provisions which read as follows: “In the case of eligible coverage months beginning before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-02-13"},"text":"February 13, 2011","children":[],"tail":"—”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/40/s241/b/2/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–40, § 241(b)(2)(C)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “72.5 percent” for “80 percent”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/344/s111/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–344, § 111(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-02-13"},"text":"February 13, 2011","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2011","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/344/s118/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–344, § 118(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-02-13"},"text":"February 13, 2011","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2011","children":[],"tail":"” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/344/s112/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–344, § 112(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-02-13"},"text":"February 13, 2011","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2011","children":[],"tail":"” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2009—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/5/s1899A/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–5, § 1899A(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “(80 percent in the case of eligible coverage months beginning before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2011","children":[],"tail":")” after “65 percent”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/5/s1899H/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–5, § 1899H(a)","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (d) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “For purposes of this section, the term ‘qualified health insurance costs credit eligibility certificate’ means any written statement that an individual is an eligible individual (as defined in section 35(c)) if such statement provides such information as the Secretary may require for purposes of this section and—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) in the case of an eligible TAA recipient (as defined in section 35(c)(2)) or an eligible alternative TAA recipient (as defined in section 35(c)(3)), is certified by the Secretary of Labor (or by any other person or entity designated by the Secretary), or","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) in the case of an eligible PBGC pension recipient (as defined in section 35(c)(4)), is certified by the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation (or by any other person or entity designated by the Secretary).”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/5/s1899B/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–5, § 1899B(a)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (e)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id47727